 economic and spiritual currents of the past forty years, emerging and adapting within an increasingly interconnected and conflicted late-capitalist world order. Based on extensive ethnographic and archival research, Hugh Urban has created a rich and powerful narrative that is a must-read for anyone interested in religion and globalization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aGurusvBiography. 0aGuruszIndia. 0aGuruszOregon. 0aNew Age movementzIndiaxHistory. 0aNew Age movementzOregonxHistoryy20th century. 7aRELIGION / Hinduism / General.2bisacsh  aanti gandhi.  abhagwan shree rajneesh.  abuddhism.  abuddhist guru.  abuddhists.  aeastern religions.  afallen gurus.  aglobal capitalism.  aglobal osho movement.  aglobal religion.  aglobalization.  agurus.  ahinduism.  aindias most dangerous guru.  anew age movement.  aoregon guru.  aosho movement.  aosho.  arajneesh community.  arajneeshpuram.  areligious sexual liberation.  arolls royce guru.  asex guru.  asex.  asexual liberation.  aspiritual leaders.  aspiritual logic of late capitalism.  atantra.  aworld religion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052028666540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096177740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520961777423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520961777/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY